Dom Moore 
IT audit reading
10/7/20

A security is the process of assessing the security of your software and system to ensure that they meet
a set of guidelines needed to ensure that your practices are inline with best practiced in relation to the
type of business and industry you are in. This process can be a daunting and intimidating process more 
companies but these audits also provide assurance or awareness for companies as to how secure their system
are therefore helping them stay ahead of or improve to prevent breaches.

There are third party software out in the market that can assist with helping maintain a systematic process
of your security and network infrastructure so when the time comes the audit process is less of a burden, 
the article talks about four types of audits Internal, external, manual and automatic each audit is specific
to the way it is conducted but the goal are the same ensure IT security compliance.
